@node main Contents

    SnoopLibs.doc, (c) ASWare 1993, by Ekke Verheul and Dirk Reisig.

    SnoopLibs was made for developers. It is a tool to find out more
    about the behaviour of a running task. It does so by making it
    possible to patch _any_ function(s) from _all_ public libraries
    and print out the calls from that task. The output format and
    type of information to print are editable by the user.

    Contents.
    ---------

    ----- How to use SnoopLibs:
    @{"     " link example} Example.
    @{"     " link gad_task} Gadgets: Task List.
    @{"     " link gad_func} Gadgets: Function List.
    @{"     " link gad_patchl} Gadgets: Patch List.
    @{"     " link gad_output} Gadgets: Output.
    @{"     " link gad_patch} Gadgets: Patch.
    @{"     " link load_lib} Menu: Load Library.
    @{"     " link output_file} Menu: Output File.
    @{"     " link tooltypes} Tooltypes.

    ----- How to add a library.
    @{"     " link add-libs} Intro
    @{"     " link fd2sl} The "fd2sl" tool.
    @{"     " link formats} Argument formats.
    @{"     " link arg_ex} Example.

    ----- Warnings.
    @{"     " link warnings} Warnings.

    ----- How to receive the source.
